message.content:
We start by calculating the average accounts receivable, then divide the Main Business Revenue by this average value.

Step 1: Determine Accounts Receivable values from the balance sheet:
• Beginning Accounts Receivable (2023-12-31): 0.00 
• Ending Accounts Receivable (2024-02-05): 10221447.35

Step 2: Compute the average:
  Average Accounts Receivable = (Beginning AR + Ending AR) / 2
   = (0.00 + 10221447.35) / 2
   = 5110723.675

Step 3: Get the sales (using Main Business Revenue from the income statement):
  Sales = 14542813.42

Step 4: Compute the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio:
  Ratio = Sales / Average Accounts Receivable
   = 14542813.42 / 5110723.675
   ≈ 2.85

Thus, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is about 2.85.
